RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 59. Claiming Purse 9000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligib ility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISS DUTTON stalked the early speed from outside, progressed three wide on the bend, fanned out further for the stretch run, took over under urging just inside the final sixteenth and began to draw off. ABBMAR broke on top, was encouraged to keep the lead and moved to the inside, drew clear on the turn, floated out entering the lane, gradually angled back to the inside, did not have enough left deep stretch but proved easily second best. MINI DRESS vied for the lead outside ABBMAR from the early going, did not keep up on the bend, came into the stretch behind the latter and had little to offer. JAMAICAN TRAFFIC was an early factor, saved ground through the turn and proved empty for the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Miss Dutton
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked outside, roused 3 wide 1/4, drew off inside last 1/16th

ENTRY.NAME: Jamaican Traffic
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, empty stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Abbmar
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent, inside, weakened late, easily best of the rest

ENTRY.NAME: Mini Dress
ENTRY.COMMENT: early speed 2 wide, gave way stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 50. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VIVA VIOLENCE rated between rivals on the backstretch, was let out three wide nearing the bend, took a clear lead, was put to urging midstretch, steadily widened command and ridden out the final sixteenth. AMARI S. well placed inside from the beginning, moved clear for second on the turn, was no match for VIVA VIOLENCE when set down for the stretch run but was unchallenged for the place. LORI ATTACK was soon outrun, though urged along early, moved to the inside with a half mile to go, came off the rail at the top of the stretch and drew off for third. DELTA LADY prompted the pace from outside but began to fade four wide on the bend. FILLY FROM ILLY was hustled to a clear early lead, challenged from both sides after two furlongs and also began to yield after three furlongs.

ENTRY.NAME: Amari S.
ENTRY.OWNER: Lynch Harry E and Couch Ron
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed, inside, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Filly From Illy
ENTRY.COMMENT: used early 2 wide

ENTRY.NAME: Viva Violence
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated between, let out 3 wide turn, urged 1/8 to 1/16

ENTRY.NAME: Lori Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, easily best of rest

ENTRY.NAME: Delta Lady
ENTRY.COMMENT: faded 4 wide turn

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 65. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WARNING LABEL was kept close from outside, went for the lead four wide on the bend, drew clear under urging upper stretch and maintained control under steady handling. AVENGING WARRIOR disputed the pace two wide between horses, could not hold back WARNING LABEL in the lane but edged ahead for the place in the late going. KANITHAPPEN broke outward, bumping STORMIN EL PRADO, raced in contention between horses, angled in some with a half mile left, was crowded briefly into the bend, lost ground fanning five wide into the stretch, rallied the last eighth and took over third nearing the sixteenth marker. STORMIN EL PRADO bumped from the rear at the break, was prominent between rivals, vied for the lead three wide on the turn, was steadied when caught in tight quarters between horses entering the lane and gradually wore down. FAITHFUL KING helped press the early pace between rivals, angled in with four furlongs to go, threw his head and became difficult to control while boxed in entering the bend, was checked hard, saved ground through the turn and gradually angled out the last furlong as he showed a willingness to run. CALL ME DROSSEL displayed early speed from inside but flattened out for the drive. There was a stewards inquiry into FAITHFUL KING'S loss of action into the turn. After their review, no change was made.

ENTRY.NAME: Call Me Drossel
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, flattened out

ENTRY.NAME: Avenging Warrior
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2 wide speed, not enough left

ENTRY.NAME: Faithful King
ENTRY.COMMENT: threw head, rank 7/16s, checked hard

ENTRY.NAME: Kanithappen
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, crowded 7/16, 3-5 path turn, gaining

ENTRY.NAME: Stormin El Prado
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3 wide bid turn, steadied 3/16s, weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: Warning Label
ENTRY.COMMENT: kept close outside, 4 wide turn, drew clear stretch, kept to task

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 4 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHERNYAHOVSKIY broke alertly, was engaged from outside on the backstretch, floated out entering the stretch, moved clear as he gradually drifted out, was all out and held on. SUPER SILVER stayed close to the early speed while just off the inside, began to angle out as he commenced his bid on the second bend, came into the stretch from path five, rallied inside the final furlong and finished on every terms with CHERNYAHOVSKIY. MEMORY BANK settled well off the inside, picked up his pace after a half mile, lost ground widest through the second turn and rallied belatedly deep stretch. TRIPLE CHROME vied for the lead outside CHERNYAHOVSKIY on the backstretch and through the second bend, was forced out to path four into the lane, began to yield, was steadied behind the latter inside the last eighth, altered in some and continued to slowly give way. There was a minus win pool of $536.90.

ENTRY.NAME: dh-Chernyahovskiy
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, drifted out stretch, held on

ENTRY.NAME: dh-Super Silver
ENTRY.COMMENT: stayed close just off rail, 3-5 path 2nd turn, up at wire

ENTRY.NAME: Memory Bank
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled outside, 4-6 path 2nd turn, gaining

ENTRY.NAME: Triple Chrome
ENTRY.OWNER: Randazzo Anthony P and Randazzo Jennifer
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied 2 wide,carried out into stretch,weakened,steadied inside 1/8

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COPPER CROSSING shared the lead from inside, did not stay with ARGYBARGY BUCK into the second bend, floated out some into the lane, took the advantage inside the last eighth and narrowly kept the latter at bay. ARGYBARGY BUCK vied for the lead from off the inside, drew clear when allowed after five furlongs, stayed just off the inside through the second turn, steadily drifted out in the lane, lost the lead, held a straight path in the waning yards but was outfinished in a game effort. GEORGE'S VISION settled inside, commenced his bid nearing the end of a half mile, progressed three wide on the second bend, bumped with STAY STRONG upper stretch, altered outside ARGYBARBGY BUCK inside the final furlong, closed in the waning yards but was too late. FUTURE VISION prominent in the second flight through the early going, did not keep up two wide on the second turn, had the inside for the stretch run and lacked a late bid. STAY STRONG raced outside FUTURE VISION for more than a half mile, moved clear for third three wide on the second bend, angled in beside COPPER CROSSING nearing the quarter pole, fanned out leaving that turn, began to yield, bumped with GEORGE'S VISION upper stretch and continued to give way. I CAN'T TELL YA was a factor from outside for a half mile then gave way.

ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-path speed, drifted out stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Copper Crossing
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, rallied stretch, led inside 1/8, held on

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 88. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 18000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF THREE RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FIVE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $15,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000 (Claiming Races For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RACETOTHEFINISH hesitated at the break, prompted the pace from inside, angled out approaching the bend, progressed three wide, took the lead outside DELIGHTFUL BREEZE midstretch, moved clear and maintained control under nearly all hand urging. AROSE FOR LYLA was soon well back, picked up her pace after a quarter mile, stayed off the rail on the turn, angled out widest upper stretch, steadily closed the gap, gained second seventy-five yards out, was too late to catch RACETOTHEFINISH but drew away for the place. ICY RIVER vied for the early lead inside DELIGHTFUL BREEZE, was bumped by the latter shortly after travelling two furlongs, did not keep up along the rail on the bend, angled outside RACETOTHEFINISH at the top of the lane and continued to yield. DELIGHTFUL BREEZE displayed early speed from outside, lugged in some to bump ICY RIVER after a quarter mile, moved clear on the turn, floated out some entering the lane, was challenged from outside and flattened out the final furlong.

ENTRY.NAME: Racetothefinish
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: hesitated start, 3-4 path turn, drew clear last 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Icy River
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, angled out upper stretch, flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Delightful Breeze
ENTRY.COMMENT: outside speed, 2-3 path turn, flattened out last 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Arose for Lyla
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside, angled out turn, 6-path rally, closing

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 7 1M Dirt CR: 89. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 16000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TWO COOKIE RULE bobbled a few strides from the gate and was allowed to settle, swiftly advanced from outside on the backstretch to gain the lead before finishing a half mile, saved ground through the second bend, moved clear entering the lane, was challenged from outside upper stretch, dug in and slowly edged ahead deep stretch. AHEADOFTHEGAME bumped at the start, soon moved to a clear lead, was overtaken from outside approaching the end of four furlongs, angled outside TWO COOKIE RULE into the second turn, rallied to challenge the latter upper stretch, fought gamely but had to settle for second best. DIAMOND DAVE broke outward, bumping AHEADOFTHEGAME, chased from just off or along the rail, came into contention while saving ground through the second bend, angled out three wide upper stretch, could only make up minor ground in the late going but was easily best of the rest. MKAR THE FAST a bit reluctant to load, retreated from inside on the backstretch, was two wide taking the second turn and had no late bid. PERFECT WAGER soon trailed, angled out widest at the halfway point, advanced four wide on the second bend, angled in beside MKAR THE FAST approaching the quarter pole, moved out four wide again upper stretch and had little to offer the rest of the way. ALLEN broke well, was three wide taking the first turn, steadily retreated from between rivals once on the backstretch, was eased in the stretch and walked off.

ENTRY.COMMENT: middle move inside, angled 3 wide stretch, best of rest
